sampleIndex3.T<-function(proj.data,ratio){
  #proj.data<-(proj.data-mean(proj.data))/sd(proj.data)
  gamma<-0.838
  a<-sqrt((1-gamma)/gamma)
  b<--sqrt(gamma/(1-gamma))
  maxI<-gamma*a*dnorm(a)+(1-gamma)*b*dnorm(b)
  index1<-(dnorm(0)-mean(dnorm(proj.data)))/(dnorm(0)-dnorm(1))
  index2<-mean(proj.data*dnorm(proj.data))**2/maxI**2
  return(ratio*index1+(1-ratio)*index2)
}


## data standardize
std.data <- function(data){
  orig.var<-var(data)
  eig.var<-eigen(orig.var)
  if(sum(eig.var$values==0)!=0){
    p<-sum(eig.var$values!=0)
    vect.temp<-eig.var$vectors[,1:p,drop=FALSE]
    val.temp<-eig.var$values[1:p]
    invvar.5<-vect.temp%*%diag(1/sqrt(val.temp),ncol=p)%*%t(vect.temp)
  } else{
    invvar.5<-eig.var$vectors%*%diag(1/sqrt(eig.var$values))%*%t(eig.var$vectors)
  }
  stddata<-apply(data,2,function(x) x-mean(x))
  stddata<-stddata%*%invvar.5
  return(stddata)
}

1974-PP for EDA

################## 1974-PP for EDA ##################
PPIndex.1974<-function(proj.data, p=0.1, R=0.1){
  trim.num <- round(length(proj.data)*p)
  trim.data <- sort(proj.data)[trim.num:(length(proj.data)-trim.num-1)]
  trim.sd <- sqrt(var(trim.data))
  
  dist.data <- dist(proj.data)
  cutoff <- quantile(dist.data, probs=R)
  local.den <- sum(dist.data[dist.data<cutoff])
  
  return(trim.sd*local.den)
}

1993-Legendre / Hermite / Natural Hermite Index

################## Legendre / Hermite  ##################
LegendreIndex <- function(proj.data){
  return(sum((proj.data-dnorm(proj.data))**2/(2*dnorm(proj.data))))
}
Huberplot(stddata,class,PPmethod="UserDef",UserDefFtn=LegendreIndex)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

HermiteIndex <- function(proj.data){
  return(sum((proj.data-dnorm(proj.data))**2))
}
Huberplot(stddata,class,PPmethod="UserDef",UserDefFtn=HermiteIndex)

  return(sum((proj.data-dnorm(proj.data))**2*dnorm(proj.data)))
}

2015-PP framework 5 classification index

########## 2015-PP framework 5 classification index ########## 
LppIndex <- function(proj.data, origData, k){
  result <- 0
  
  for (i in 1:length(proj.data)){
    # k neighborhood data's index
    knn.ind <- order((origData[i,1]-origData[,1])^2+(origData[i,2]-origData[,2])^2)[2:(k+1)]
    for (j in knn.ind){
      result <- result + (proj.data[i]-proj.data[j])^2 * exp(sum((origData[i,]-origData[j,])^2))
    }
  }
  #print(1/result)
  return(1/result)
}

Huberplot(stddata,class,PPmethod="UserDef",UserDefFtn=LppIndex, origData=stddata, k=10)

2022-Hole or Grain? Section Pursuit index

########## Section Pursuit index ########## 
## Huberplot   theta    
huber <- function (origdata2D, origclass, PPmethod = "LDA", weight = TRUE, 
    r = 1, lambda = 0.5, opt.proj = TRUE, UserDefFtn = NULL, 
    ...) 
{
    index <- NULL
    best.proj <- NULL
    best.index <- 0
    origdata2D <- as.matrix(origdata2D)
    for (i in 0:360) {
        theta <- pi/180 * i
        proj.data <- matrix(cos(theta) * origdata2D[, 1] + sin(theta) * 
            origdata2D[, 2])
        proj <- matrix(c(cos(theta), sin(theta)), ncol = 1)
        if (PPmethod == "LDA") {
            newindex <- LDAindex(origclass, origdata2D, proj = proj, 
                weight = weight)
        }
        else if (PPmethod == "PDA") {
            newindex <- PDAindex(origclass, origdata2D, proj, 
                weight = weight, lambda = lambda)
        }
        else if (PPmethod == "Lr") {
            newindex <- Lrindex(origclass, origdata2D, proj, 
                weight = weight, r = r)
        }
        else if (PPmethod == "GINI") {
            newindex <- GINIindex1D(origclass, origdata2D, proj)
        }
        else if (PPmethod == "ENTROPY") {
            newindex <- ENTROPYindex1D(origclass, origdata2D, 
                proj)
        }
        else if (PPmethod == "UserDef") {
            newindex <- UserDefFtn(proj.data, origdata2D, theta, ...)
        }
        index <- c(index, newindex)
    }
    sel.index <- which(index[1:360] > signif(max(index), 6) - 
        1e-06)
    theta.best.all <- pi/180 * (sel.index - 1)
    theta.best <- theta.best.all[1]
    proj.data.best <- matrix(cos(theta.best) * origdata2D[, 1] + 
        sin(theta.best) * origdata2D[, 2])
    index.best <- max(index)
    range <- round(max(index) - min(index), 5)
    if (range == 0) {
        PPindex <- rep(4, length(index))
    }
    else {
        PPindex <- (index - min(index))/range * 2 + 3
    }
    data.circle <- NULL
    data.index <- NULL
    for (i in 1:361) {
        theta <- pi/180 * (i - 1)
        data.index <- rbind(data.index, c(PPindex[i] * cos(theta), 
            PPindex[i] * sin(theta)))
        data.circle <- rbind(data.circle, c(4 * cos(theta), 4 * 
            sin(theta)))
    }
    maxdiff <- max(c(diff(range(origdata2D[, 1])), diff(range(origdata2D[, 
        2]))))
    orig.scaled <- apply(origdata2D, 2, function(x) (x - mean(x))/maxdiff * 
        3.5)
    data.cX <- data.circle[, 1]
    data.cY <- data.circle[, 2]
    data.X <- data.index[, 1]
    data.Y <- data.index[, 2]
    plot.data <- data.frame(data.cX, data.cY, data.X, data.Y)
    x <- orig.scaled[, 1]
    y <- orig.scaled[, 2]
    group <- origclass
    point.data <- data.frame(x, y, group)
    min.X <- min(unlist(plot.data))
    max.X <- max(unlist(plot.data))
    P1 <- ggplot(data = plot.data, aes(x = data.X, y = data.Y)) + 
        geom_path() + geom_path(aes(x = data.cX, y = data.cY), 
        linetype = "dashed") + geom_point(data = point.data, 
        aes(x = x, y = y, color = group, shape = group)) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = NULL) + 
        scale_y_continuous(breaks = NULL) + xlab("") + 
        ylab("") + coord_fixed() + theme_bw() + theme(panel.border = element_blank())
    if (opt.proj) {
        P1 <- P1 + geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = sin(theta.best)/cos(theta.best))
        if (length(theta.best.all) > 1) 
            for (i in 2:length(theta.best.all)) P1 <- P1 + geom_abline(intercept = 0, 
                slope = sin(theta.best.all[i])/cos(theta.best.all[i]), 
                linetype = "dashed")
    }
    best.proj.data <- proj.data.best
    group <- origclass
    hist.data <- data.frame(best.proj.data, group)
    P2 <- ggplot(data = hist.data, aes(x = best.proj.data, group = group)) + 
        geom_histogram(aes(fill = group), position = "stack")
    gridExtra::grid.arrange(P1, P2, nrow = 1)
}

HoleIndex <- function(proj.data, origdata2D, theta, cutoff=0.2){
  newdf <- data.frame(proj.data)
  newdf$h <- sin(theta) * origdata2D[, 1] + cos(theta) * origdata2D[, 2]
  newdf$kbins <- cut(proj.data, seq(min(proj.data), max(proj.data), length.out=5))
  newdf$sc <- ifelse(newdf$h<quantile(newdf$h, probs=cutoff), "s", "c")
  result <- newdf %>% group_by(kbins) %>% summarise(s=sum(sc=="s"), c=sum(sc=="c"))
  return(sum(result$s-result$c))
}

huber(stddata,class,PPmethod="UserDef",UserDefFtn=HoleIndex)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

GrainIndex <- function(proj.data, origdata2D, theta, cutoff=0.2){
  newdf <- data.frame(proj.data)
  newdf$h <- sin(theta) * origdata2D[, 1] + cos(theta) * origdata2D[, 2]
  newdf$kbins <- cut(proj.data, seq(min(proj.data), max(proj.data), length.out=5))
  newdf$sc <- ifelse(newdf$h<quantile(newdf$h, probs=cutoff), "s", "c")
  result <- newdf %>% group_by(kbins) %>% summarise(s=sum(sc=="s"), c=sum(sc=="c"))
  return(sum(result$c-result$s))
}
huber(stddata,class,PPmethod="UserDef",UserDefFtn=GrainIndex)
